FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1771876127
OL,3,CSouthern drivers rated 'worst' in
OL,4,CEngland as bad behaviour puts lives at
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FTailgating alone has been linked to
OL,8,F222 fatal or serious collisions on
OL,9,Froads in the South East last year. It
OL,10,Fis an offence, with drivers risking a
OL,11,Ffine and three penalty points on their
OL,12,Flicence.
OL,14,FNational Highways is now urging people
OL,15,Fto think about their road etiquette,
OL,16,Fwith poor driving a 'real concern' for
OL,17,Froad safety.
OL,19,FWatch: A driver was caught by Thames
OL,20,FValley Police tailgating in the
OL,21,Foutside lane.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1771876127
OL,3,CSouthern drivers rated 'worst' in
OL,4,CEngland as bad behaviour puts lives at
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FAcross England, 27% of drivers
OL,8,Fadmitted that running late was the
OL,9,Fbiggest trigger for poor driving. A
OL,10,Ffurther 20% said tiredness made their
OL,11,Fdriving worse, whilst 16% blamed peak-
OL,12,Ftime commuting.
OL,14,FOnly 40% of drivers rated road
OL,15,Fetiquette in the region as good,
OL,16,Fmeaning London and the South East
OL,17,Franks sixth out of six regions across
OL,18,FEngland in National Highways' new
OL,19,F'manners map'.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1771876127
OL,3,CSouthern drivers rated 'worst' in
OL,4,CEngland as bad behaviour puts lives at
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FIt hopes that by highlighting poor
OL,8,Fstandards of driving, motorists will
OL,9,Freconsider how they act on the regions
OL,10,Froads, and be more polite and
OL,11,Fconsiderate.
OL,13,FColin Stevenson, Road Safety
OL,14,FInformation Lead at National Highways,
OL,15,Fsaid: "While the regional picture
OL,16,Fvaries it's clear that tailgating
OL,17,Fremains a real concern.
OL,26,@wD@GOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1771876127
OL,3,CSouthern drivers rated 'worst' in
OL,4,CEngland as bad behaviour puts lives at
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,F"It may seem harmless, but it can put
OL,8,Feveryone on the road at risk.
OL,9,FFollowing too closely means there is
OL,10,Fless time to react and stop safely if
OL,11,Fthe vehicle in front slows down or
OL,12,Fstops.
OL,14,F"Leaving a safe gap makes driving
OL,15,Fsafer, keeps traffic moving more
OL,16,Fsmoothly, and is a simple courtesy
OL,17,Fthat helps everyone feel more relaxed
OL,18,Fbehind the wheel. A good rule of thumb
OL,19,Fis the two-second rule, which should
OL,20,Fbe doubled in wet conditions or when
OL,21,Fvisibility is reduced."
OL,26,@vD@AOU}D@WO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
